 A: The greatest common divisor \(\gcd(100, 45) = 5\), computed as follows:

\[
\begin{align*}
100 &= 2 \times 45 + 10 \\
45 &= 4 \times 10 + 5 \\
10 &= 2 \times 5 + 0 \quad \leftarrow \text{Stop!}
\end{align*}
\] 

Thus, the sequence of remainders is \( r_0 = 100, r_1 = 45, r_2 = 10, r_3 = 5, r_4 = 0 \).
